<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Wireless on Learn, Converse, Share</title><link>http://jmeridth.com/tags/wireless/</link><description>Recent content in Wireless on Learn, Converse, Share</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><lastBuildDate>Tue, 05 Feb 2013 00:00:00 -0600</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="http://jmeridth.com/tags/wireless/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Renew DHCP Lease on Ubuntu VM After Moving Between Wireless Networks</title><link>http://jmeridth.com/posts/renew-dhcp-lease-on-ubuntu-vm-after-moving-between-wireless-networks/</link><pubDate>Tue, 05 Feb 2013 00:00:00 -0600</pubDate><guid>http://jmeridth.com/posts/renew-dhcp-lease-on-ubuntu-vm-after-moving-between-wireless-networks/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;TL;DR&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;sudo dhclient -r &lt;span class="o"&gt;[&lt;/span&gt;eth0&lt;span class="o"&gt;]&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="p"&gt;&amp;amp;&lt;/span&gt;amp&lt;span class="p"&gt;;&amp;amp;&lt;/span&gt;amp&lt;span class="p"&gt;;&lt;/span&gt; sudo dhclient &lt;span class="o"&gt;[&lt;/span&gt;eth0&lt;span class="o"&gt;]&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;I add that command as an alias to my ~/.bashrc file&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="nb"&gt;alias&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="nv"&gt;resetdhcp&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="s1"&gt;&amp;#39;sudo dhclient -r eth0 &amp;amp;amp;&amp;amp;amp; sudo dhclient eth0&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;then resourced it so I could use it in the bash session I was in&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex="0"&gt;&lt;code&gt;source ~/.bashrc
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;p&gt;I constantly have my Ubuntu VM (VirtualBox) running on my Windows laptop and dock/undock it between work and home. Obviously those are two different wireless networks. Well, I was unable to find a dhcp renewal command that would work until today (look above).&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>